## 2. Execution Boundaries & Workflow Constraints

- **Monorepo Fencing (CRITICAL):** Before executing any file creation, read, or modification, you MUST explicitly identify the target application/package within the Turborepo (e.g., `apps/commitpayapp`). You are STRICTLY FORBIDDEN from modifying files in sibling directories or other apps. You must verify that all absolute file paths start with the intended target app prefix before execution.

- **Core Infrastructure (HALT & AWAIT GO):** You must NEVER alter `/packages/types`, Firebase DB rules, Auth logic, or Edge functions without my explicit "GO".

- **Self-Audit:** Before halting to request my "GO", you must act as a Paranoid Staff Engineer. Aggressively critique your proposed architecture against the 401 Rule, App Router boundaries, and strict schema alignment. Present the tradeoffs to me alongside your proposal.

- **Environment Variables:** Always flag required environment variable changes pre-deploy.

- **UI/CRUD (AUTO-EXECUTE):** You may auto-execute standard UI and CRUD operations only after generating a blueprint.

